description:
&lt;p&gt;Black Country Pathology Services seek to recruit an enthusiastic individual to join our busy department as a senior Medical Laboratory Assistant.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role will be based at our Sandwell laboratory in the routine automated Biochemistry area. It will involve working with our robotic sample handler which introduces samples to the system and retrieves samples to go elsewhere. This requires an individual with dexterity who can work under pressure. Also as part of the role is the operation and set up of other bench top equipment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The hours of work are Monday-Friday with rotational shifts of 8:00 - 16:00 and 14:00 - 22:00 and the post is paid at AfC band 3 with a salary of £18,813 - £20,795 pa pro rata.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will have had at least 12 months experience working in a clinical NHS lab. To have had previous experience of working with analysers or undertaking complex biomedical analysis will be an advantage but not essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameJaspal GhaleJob titleDiscipline Lead for Clinical BiochemistryEmail addressjaspal.ghale@nhs.netTelephone number01902 695291Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
